'''Petty apartheid''' was the term used to refer to certain relatively minor restrictions maintained during the apartheid era in South Africa. <ref name=EB>"Apartheid", ''Encyclopaedia Britannica''.</ref>  The maintenance of separate facilities for racial groups was an example of petty apartheid.<ref name=Hazlett>Hazlett, Thomas W. [http://www.econlib.org/library/ENC/Apartheid.html "Apartheid"], ''The Concise Encyclopedia of Economics''.</ref>

